**Idea:** Solve [LC 108. Convert Sorted Array to Binary Search Tree](https://leetcode.com/problems/convert-sorted-array-to-binary-search-tree/discuss/1418449/Java-or-Recursive) before this problem to understand the concept

**Method 1:** Memoization/Top Down DP gets TLE but AC if memoization is removed.
**T/S:** O(n\xB2)/O(n)
```
public int numTrees(int n) {
	return numTrees(n, new HashMap<>());
}

private int numTrees(int n, Map<Integer, Integer> map) {
	if (n <= 1)
		return 1;
	if (map.containsKey(n))
		return map.get(n);

	var numTrees = 0;
	for (var i = 1; i <= n; i++)
		numTrees += numTrees(i - 1) * numTrees(n - i);

	map.put(n, numTrees);
	return numTrees;
}
```
*Same as above, using streams, but without memoization.* TLE
```
public int numTrees(int n) {
	return n <= 1 ? 1 : IntStream.rangeClosed(1, n)
								 .map(i -> numTrees(i - 1) * numTrees(n - i))
								 .sum();
}
```

**Method 2:** Tabulation. Same idea, just bottom-up DP.
**T/S:** O(n\xB2)/O(n)
```
public int numTrees(int n) {
	var dp = new int[n + 1];
	dp[0] = dp[1] = 1;

	for (var i = 2; i <= n; i++)
		for (var j = 1; j <= i; j++)
			dp[i] += dp[j - 1] * dp[i - j];
	return dp[n];
}
```

