solutions.content:
Based on Multinomial theorem.
Each binary tree can be represented as an array along with null values. Now, if n=N, then the array consists of numbers 1...N and N+1 ```null``` values, that is array for N=3 will be 
```[1,2,3,null,null,null,null]```.
Now, 1...N must be in order and you can place ```null``` values in the spaces between the numbers. That is,
```[some null values],1,[some null values],2,[some null values],3,[some null values]...```
Now, let a1,a2,a3,...a(N+1) represent number of null values within gaps.
there are N+1 gaps and a1+a2+...+a(N+1)
After applying multinomial theorem we obtain result as ```(2N C N)/(N+1)```

```
class Solution {
public:
    int numTrees(int n) {
        long long int p = 1;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            p*=(n+i);
            p/=i;
        }
        p/=(n+1);
        return p;
    }
};
```

