Idea:
	each time pick a number from 1 to n to be the root of current tree, and divide the whole tree into two subtrees and solve the question recursively. To avoid duplicate calculation, using a hashmap to record completed results.
```
class Solution {
private:
    unordered_map<int, int> m{{0,1},{1,1}};
public:
    int numTrees(int n) {
        if (m.count(n)) return m[n];
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++)
            sum += numTrees(i - 1) * numTrees(n - i);
        m[n] = sum;
        return sum;
    }
};
```

