Explanation:
They key is to find out that the maximum number in a BST is always the right most one : 
Let NT be a tree made of N element
To get an N+1 element trees from NT, I need to find out where can I insert element N+1 in NT
=> I can replace every element of the right most branch.

eg: if I have 

    1
      \
        3
       /
     2

I can insert 4 these ways : 

     position    0              1                   2                  3

              4                   1                  1                    1
            /                      \                 \                     \
          1                         4                 3                     3
            \                      /                   \                  /   \
              3                 3                        4               2      4
             /                  /                       /
           2                 2                        2


Then we need to find the DP recurrence : 
Let N(i) be the number of possible tree made of i element.
to get N(i+1) we to need to take every tree of N(i) and insert i+1 on every possible location on the rightmost branch.
we can use the previous result to do so : 

 - when i+1 is in position 0, there are N(i) * N(0) results : every tree
   made of 1 element below, and every tree made of 0 element above 
 - when i+1 is in position 1, there are N(i-1) * N(1) results : every tree
   made of i-1 element below, and every tree made of 1 element above
 - when i+1 is in position 1, there are N(i-2) * N(2) results : every
   tree made of i-2 elements below, an every tree made of 2 elements
   above .
 - etc

therefore we have 

       for(int i = 2; i <= n; i++){
           for(int j=0; j<i ; j++){
                arr[i] += arr[i-j-1]* arr[j];
            }
        }

Now we just need to fill the initial cases : 

        arr[0] = 1; 
        arr[1] = 1; 

Space complexity : O(n)
Time Complexity : O(n^2)

