solutions.content:
```
F(k) = 0 * Bk[0] + 1 * Bk[1] + ... + (n-1) * Bk[n-1]
F(k-1) = 0 * Bk-1[0] + 1 * Bk-1[1] + ... + (n-1) * Bk-1[n-1]
       = 0 * Bk[1] + 1 * Bk[2] + ... + (n-2) * Bk[n-1] + (n-1) * Bk[0]
```
Then,
```
F(k) - F(k-1) = Bk[1] + Bk[2] + ... + Bk[n-1] + (1-n)Bk[0]
              = (Bk[0] + ... + Bk[n-1]) - nBk[0]
              = sum - nBk[0]
```
Thus,
```
F(k) = F(k-1) + sum - nBk[0]
```

What is Bk[0]?
```
k = 0; B[0] = A[0];
k = 1; B[0] = A[len-1];
k = 2; B[0] = A[len-2];
...
```
```java
int allSum = 0;
int len = A.length;
int F = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
    F += i * A[i];
    allSum += A[i];
}
int max = F;
for (int i = len - 1; i >= 1; i--) {
    F = F + allSum - len * A[i];
    max = Math.max(F, max);
}
return max;   
```

