eg- A = [4, 3, 2, 6]

F(0) = 0A + 1B + 2C +3D
F(1) = 0D + 1A + 2B +3C
F(2) = 0C + 1D + 2A +3B
F(3) = 0B + 1C + 2D +3A

**sum = 1A + 1B + 1C + 1D**

F(1)-F(0) = a+b+c-3d
				= a+b+c+d - 4d
				= sum - n * Bk[0];
**F(1) = F(0) + sum - n*Bk[0]**
*(where B[0] is the first element when array is rotated k-times).*

Similarly, 
F(1) = F(0) + sum - 4D
F(2) = F(1) + sum - 4C
F(3) = F(2) + sum - 4B

**So,**
```
F(k) = F(k-1) + sum - nBk[0]
```

**What is Bk[0]?**
```
k = 0; B[0] = A[0];
k = 1; B[0] = A[len-1];
k = 2; B[0] = A[len-2];
```


