# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
# Maths Approach
F(0)=0*a0 + 1*a1 + 2*a2 + 3*a3 +.....+n-1*a[n-1].
F(1) = 0*a[n-1]+ 1*a0 + 2*a1 + 3*a2 + 4*a3 +.....+n-1*a[n-2].

Now, Subtract F(1)-F(0)
F(1)-F(0)=a0 + a1 + a2 + ...+a[n-2] -(n-1)*a[n-1];
F(1)-F(0)=a0 + a1 + a2 + ... +a[n-2] + a[n-1] - n*a[n-1];
Now, F(1)-F(0)= Summation of all elements of array - n*a[n-1];
F(1)=F(0)+Summation of all elements of array - n*a[n-1];

Similarly, F(2) = F(1)+Summation of all elements of array - n*a[n-2];
           F(3)= F(2)+Summation of all elements of array - n*a[n-3];

and so on..

Store the max values for every function u will get the answer in the end.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Code the above maths algo in code.
**Steps to Code.**
1. First calculate the F(0) and sum of all elements of the array and initialise the answer with F(0).
2. Take prev variable and store the F(0) in it.
3. Now loop from i=1 to i=n-1 
4. Keep finding F(i) = prev + sum -n*(arr[n-i]);
5. Keep updating the answer and prev  value.
6. In the end u will get the answer




# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

