---

Not easy to observe at begin, taking 3 elements `[ a, b, c ]` will solve the problem

There is a bug in the problem, raised a bug - https://github.com/LeetCode-Feedback/LeetCode-Feedback/issues/3893

---

**Algo:**
- Fully based on below observation
- Assume 3 elements `[ a, b, c ]`
- Calculate `F(0) = 0xa + 1xb + 2xc`
  - Now come from reverse
    - Caculate `F(2)`, it is based on `F(0)`
    - Similarly `F(1)` will be based on `F(2)`

**Observation**

```
// -----------------------
// a    b    c
// -----------------------
//                                  so sum = a+b+c
// -----------------------
//      b   2c      F(0)
// a   2b           F(1)    this is same as .. 3*b  -a-b-c(-sum)  + (2a+c)(F(2)) = 2a+c
// 2a        c      F(2)    this is same as .. 3*a  -a-b-c(-sum)  + (b+2c)(F(0)) = 2a+c
// -----------------------
```

Hope it is simple to understand.

