Use a monotonic increasing/decreasing stack can solve multiple problems in O(n), for example, find the longest increasing/decreasing sequence, find the first smaller/bigger element to the left/right. This question is one of the application of using monotonic stack.
```
public class Solution {
    public int[] nextGreaterElement(int[] findNums, int[] nums) {
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();

        for (int num : nums) {
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() < num) {
                map.put(stack.pop(), num);
            }
            stack.push(num);
        }

        int[] res = new int[findNums.length];
        for (int i = 0; i < findNums.length; i++) {
            res[i] = map.getOrDefault(findNums[i], -1);
        }
        return res;
    }
}
