Walk through `nums1` 
Walk *backwards* (we only care about elements to the right) through `nums2` until you get to the current value from `nums1` (`i`) 
Store *any* values greater than `i` in `x` (by replacing) because we want the element *closest* to `i` 
Once we've reached the value in `nums2` that equals `i` we can break and push `x` to our output array.

If this helped you, please upvote! Thanks.

```
function nextGreaterElement(nums1: number[], nums2: number[]): number[] {
    let out = []
    for (let i of nums1) {
        let x = -1
        for (let j = nums2.length-1; nums2[j]!=i; j--) {
            if (nums2[j] > i) x = nums2[j] 
        }
        out.push(x)
    }
    return out
};
```

