# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
A slight modification of [Next Greater Element-2 Problem](https://leetcode.com/problems/next-greater-element-ii/).

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- The task is to find the next greater element for each element in nums 1 from nums2.
- So first find next greater element for each element in nums2 and store it in map.
- Then iterate over each element in nums1 and use the value stored in map to fill the result vector.
- The problem is prettt straight-forward but the challenge here is to *do these mappings from nums2 to map and then use this to find required answer*.
- I tried to code it as simple as possible. Any optimizations for this code will be appreciated.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    unordered_map<int,int> m;
    void findNGE(vector<int>& v){
        stack<int>s;
        for(int i=v.size()-1;i>=0;--i){
            while(!s.empty() and s.top()<= v[i]) s.pop();
            int res= s.empty()? -1: s.top();
            m[v[i]]=res;
            s.push(v[i]);
        }
    }
    vector<int> nextGreaterElement(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        vector<int>res;
        findNGE(nums2);
        for(auto x: nums1) res.push_back(m[x]);
        return res;
    }
};
```

