The map stores the value of an array as key and in value it use an int[] of size three whose 0th element is left most position of that element, 1st element contains right most position of that element and 2nd position contains the degree of that element.
max variable is used to store the max degree and res is used to store the result.
```
class Solution {
    public int findShortestSubArray(int[] nums) {
        Map<Integer, int[]> m = new HashMap<>();
        int max = 0;
        int res = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            int a = nums[i];
            if(!m.containsKey(a)){
                m.put(a, new int[]{i,i,1});
                if(max == 0) max = 1;
                if(res == 0) res = 1;
            }else{
