# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Store first index of all the unique elements in a frequency vector and store the maximum frequency in a variable. Use a hash map to store frequency of all elements, whenever the frequency of the element becomes equal to the maximum frequency, calculate the size of sub-array it is present in. Calculate the minimum size of sub-array which is present with the stated condition.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Intution contains the approach in itself. The code is attached for reference.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nlogn)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

