I use collections.Counter() to find the degree of the array ```nums```. 
Then if an element of ```nums``` has the same degree I add all occurrences (index) of the element into a dictionary.
The result is calculated as a minimum between the last and the first occurrences for every element in the dictionary

````
from collections import Counter

class Solution:
    def findShortestSubArray(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:

        counter = Counter(nums)
        degree = counter.most_common(1)[0][1]

        positions = dict()
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            num = nums[i]
            if counter[num] == degree:
                if num not in positions:
                    positions[num] = [i]
                else:
                    positions[num] += [i]

        res = 100000
        for i in positions:
            res = min(res, positions[i][-1] - positions[i][0])
        return res+1
		```

