solutions.content:
It would have been easy if only one element had the max frequency 
But more than one elements can have max frequency
So the best way to do this question is 
Find the max frequency & starting and ending index of every element 
Now iterate the frequency map
If you find an element that has max frequency find it's starting and ending index that we stored earlier

```
class Solution {
public:
    int findShortestSubArray(vector<int>& a) {

        int n = a.size();

        map<int,int> m;
        map<int, pair<int,int>> se;

        int mf = 0;

        int ans = n;

        for(int i = 0 ; i < n ; i++){

            m[a[i]]++;
            mf = max(mf,m[a[i]]);

            if(se.find(a[i]) != se.end())
                se[a[i]].second = i;    
            else    
                se[a[i]] = {i,i};

        }

        for(auto i:m){

            if(i.second == mf){

                auto indices = se[i.first];

                int s = indices.first;
                int e = indices.second;

                ans = min(ans, e-s+1);

            }

        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

